        </How>
        <Summary>
            <p>
                In this article we learn't how LINQ <Highlight>Execution</Highlight> and <Highlight>Operators</Highlight> work. We saw how
                <Highlight>Deferred</Highlight> and <Highlight>Immediate</Highlight> execution works along with <Highlight>Streaming</Highlight>
                and <Highlight>Non-Streaming</Highlight> operators. We learnt the advantages of deferred execution and how to use <Highlight>yield</Highlight>
                keyword in streaming operations with a live demo. With this I'm completing my LINQ series. Feel free to checkout LINQ learning path in
                <NavLink href="channels/linq">LINQ Channel</NavLink>.
            </p>
        </Summary>
